SUBENT        F0464001   20260210   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                  6         11
TITLE      Neutron and gamma rays from the alpha-particle
           bombardment of 9Be, 10B, 11B, 13C and 18O
AUTHOR     (T.W.Bonner,A.A.Kraus,J.B.Marion,J.P.Schiffer)
INSTITUTE  (1USARIC)
REFERENCE  (J,PR,102,1348,1956)
FACILITY   (VDG,1USARIC)
HISTORY    (19860820C)
           (20030503U) Reaction code changed in sub.012,013
           (20260210A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           The accuracy of data presentation has been revised in
           all Subents.
ENDBIB              11
NOCOMMON             0          0
ENDSUBENT           14
SUBENT        F0464002   20260210   20260508   20260508       F108
BIB                  7         15
REACTION   (4-BE-9(A,N)6-C-12,,DA)
SAMPLE     Target was about 10 keV thick to 2 MeV alphas
DETECTOR   (TELES,LONGC,BF3) The neutron detector used was
           modified long-counter with paraffin moderator 5 inches
           in diam. and 5 inches long surrounding a BF3 counter
           which was 1 inch in diam. and extended to the front
           surface of the paraffin.
REL-REF    (A,,Halpern,J,PR,76,248,1949) A cross section of
           0.40 barn at 5.3 MeV and 0.13 barn at 1.9 MeV are given
ERR-ANALYS Statistical errors are less than or equal to the
           diameter of the points.
           (DATA-ERR) No information about source of uncertainty
STATUS     (CURVE,,T.W.Bonner+,J,PR,102,1348,1956) Fig. 1
HISTORY    (20260210A) SD: BIB updated. EN-ERR -> EN-ERR-DIG;
           DATA-ERR -> ERR-DIG; DATA-ERR1 -> DATA-ERR.
ENDBIB              15
