           (NAICR) A 1 in. x 1 in. NaI crystal mounted on a
           DuMont 6292 photomultiplier tube was used for the
           gamma-ray detector.
COMMENT    It is estimated that at most 10% of the gamma-ray
           yield could be caused by neutrons in the NaI crystal.
MONITOR    The cross section calibration was made at 1.9-MeV
           resonance using both weighed evaporated Be targets
           on 0.002 in. aluminum foil and a thick Be target. A
           stopping power of 1.40 MeV/mg/cm2 was used for 1.9 MeV
           alphas in 9Be.
ERR-ANALYS Statistical errors are less than or equal to the
           diameter of the points on the fig.
STATUS     (CURVE,,T.W.Bonner+,J,PR,102,1348,1956) Fig. 2
HISTORY    (20260210A) SD:  BIB updated. EN-ERR -> EN-ERR-DIG;
           DATA-ERR -> ERR-DIG.
ENDBIB              23
COMMON               2          3
EN-ERR-DIG ERR-DIG
MEV        MB/SR
 0.015        0.02
ENDCOMMON            3
